    "For polynomial functions, an exact output is obtained using L 1 with an R 2 = 1.0, whereas only approximate output is obtained using L 2.",
    "In the latter case, the quality of the fit depends on the size of the training data set.",
    "An exemplary result is shown in Fig. 4 for f (x) = x + x 2 + x 3.",
    "Points represent the (test) data of the input file, i.e., X; the red curve represents f(x) as a function of x, and the blue and black dashed curves represent the predicted function f (x) obtained using L 1 and L 2 respectively.",
